Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.06,0:00:12.61,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Mr. Rohan, thanks for meeting with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.16,0:00:14.86,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Pretty nice out today, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.29,0:00:18.16,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Whatcha reading about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:20.37,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,De Staël.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:22.12,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,De Staël?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.12,0:00:24.00,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,That a new band or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.90,0:00:27.02,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,A painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.63,0:00:31.10,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,He was a painter from Russia who died in 1955.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.34,0:00:34.38,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Listen, Kaigamori...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.97,0:00:40.35,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\an8}Arriving late to a meeting is unacceptable, \N as you're clearly well aware...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.78,0:00:44.39,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,...but arriving six minutes {\i1}early{\i0} for \N a meeting with a comics artist?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:47.73,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Isn't that rather unbecoming for an editor?{"Poor planning"? He says it's bad MANNERS. Pretty significant difference there if you ask me. Rather liberal suggestion that still maintains the point he be making: "Do editors have no concept of manners?!"-Starfish}{Seconding that with just an interrogation mark for punctuation. - Toa}{Rohan's inflection does merit use of "?!"; the のか at the end of his line indicates he's expecting an answer, and his tone flat out demands one. However, I wouldn't be heartbroken if a simple question mark is preferred. And the TL rules on this one (plus I like his take given the intended meaning). -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.65,0:00:52.28,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,S-Sorry about that... \NSo showing up early is rude, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.28,0:00:54.57,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Fortunately I'm rather equable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.57,0:00:59.16,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's go over my \Nupcoming sixty-one page one-shot together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.16,0:01:02.00,Main,Tamami,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you, Mr. Rohan! \NWe're big fans of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.00,0:01:03.83,Main,Otoishi,0,0,0,,Can we have your autograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:05.83,Main,Otoishi,0,0,0,,Make mine out to Otoishi, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.83,0:01:08.50,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Knock it off! \N He's not doing a signing right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.13,0:01:12.67,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,We're in the middle of a meeting! \N He doesn't have time!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.67,0:01:14.20,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I already finished them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:18.60,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Don't presume I'm as slow as other artists.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.60,0:01:20.93,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Take my autograph with special thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.28,0:01:25.89,Main,Tamami,0,0,0,,Did he just make these awesome \N drip paintings... with coffee?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.89,0:01:27.90,Main,Otoishi,0,0,0,,Thank you a bunch! \NWe appreciate the hell out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.90,0:01:29.85,Main,Tamami,0,0,0,,Holy crap! Holy crap! Holy crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.40,0:01:36.20,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,By the way, may we discuss my \Ncurrent circumstances before we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.20,0:01:36.90,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.41,0:01:42.29,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,To be frank, it's about money. \NMore specifically, regarding my pay. Do you follow?{Not sure about "frank" here... "To get straight to the point" or something like that, maybe? -Starfish}{That's exactly what being "frank" is about -- he's being straightforward (about his situation and what he wants). -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.12,0:01:44.87,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Will you allow me an advance?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.87,0:01:46.83,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I just recently declared bankruptcy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.83,0:01:47.54,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.54,0:01:51.79,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I have no outstanding debts,\N but I'm currently homeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.79,0:01:52.67,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.67,0:01:56.92,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I'm staying at my friend Koichi's house,\N and I lack a desk for drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.92,0:01:57.84,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Huh? {Huh???}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.84,0:02:03.43,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I had to sell my Sailor Moon figurines,\N Led Zeppelin record jackets, and Rurouni Kenshin comics. {Huh???}{D:}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.43,0:02:06.68,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Are you serious?! \N You have nowhere to work?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.68,0:02:07.81,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,You're broke?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.81,0:02:12.11,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,But weren't you planning to build a \Nvilla on the mountain you just bought?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:13.44,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Let me explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.44,0:02:17.40,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I was researching the supernatural beings \N living on the mountain for the comic I was drawing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.40,0:02:20.74,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Then a development company made plans \Nto build a resort trail right through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.11,0:02:25.66,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,So naturally, I purchased six mountains in \N the surrounding area to put a stop to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.66,0:02:28.71,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I had to buy up as much land as possible, right?{I mean that seems to be the implication but the actual phrasing is just "I had to buy as much area as possible, right?" -Starfish}{Change "area" to "land" and we have a deal with LS' take. -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.71,0:02:30.63,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,In order to foil their plan, obviously.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.51,0:02:37.52,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,But now that the resort trail isn't being made, \N I essentially own worthless land.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.34,0:02:41.72,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Those six mountains \N may as well be piles of dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.72,0:02:43.55,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,All this to say: I'm broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:45.64,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,So will you grant me an advance or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:47.64,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,L-Let me get this straight...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.42,0:02:51.85,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,You bought those mountains to \N gather reference material for your comic?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:52.36,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.36,0:02:53.86,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Not as an investment?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:56.53,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Precisely.\N My work requires reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.53,0:02:59.03,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,All to gather reference material \N on supernatural beings?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:00.45,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Enough questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.45,0:03:04.41,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Consider the consequences had the trail been built! \N The supernatural beings may have fled!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.85,0:03:07.45,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,All my efforts would have been for naught!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.42,0:03:13.25,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey, hey! \NWhat's with the look?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.25,0:03:15.04,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Are you intentionally averting your gaze?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.04,0:03:17.17,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Ah hah! You are! {Be sure to check for spelling consistency with any other potential uses of "Aha". The index provided no results for a bunch of spellings ("Aha", "A-ha", "Ah-hah", "Ah hah") so it's possible this is the first time it's been used, but pointing it out regardless and also in case one of these (or another form I'm not considering) is considered a more "correct" way of rendering exclamation. - Toa}{I think this is legitimately the only time we've ever had someone exclaim, "Aha!" That said, hyphenation for me depends on whether or not the first "a" in "aha" is drawn out, or if there's a slight pause between "a" and "ha". If either situation is true, I hyphenate. -JMFW}{Changed it to the one I liked the most. May as well establish the standard now -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:21.63,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Do you believe I'm of unsound mind, \N Mr. Editor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:22.43,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Consider this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.43,0:03:29.43,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Buying supercars or building expensive basement game rooms \N aren't the only ways comics artists spend their money!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.08,0:03:33.48,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Besides, they were actually there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.48,0:03:35.61,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I gathered all the material I needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.79,0:03:41.05,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Listen closely. Your editorial department, \Nand no one else, will be told of this matter.{Completely re-TL'd this line because the previous phrasing was, just, absolutely not what he said. Obviously this phrasing is now super jank, but... I wanted to be as clear as possible.-Starfish} {I think it reads well. If you want to make it less weird sounding, "I will tell just your editorial department, and no one else, about this" maybe? -Axel}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.68,0:03:44.29,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,{\i1}Th-They{\i0} were there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.08,0:03:47.12,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,{\i1}What{\i0} was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.12,0:03:50.37,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,Have you listened to a single word I've said?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.37,0:03:52.25,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,I witnessed it with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.25,0:03:54.70,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,The supernatural beings of Mutsukabe Hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:03:58.50,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,They're there at this very moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.29,0:04:01.97,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Mr. Rohan...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.81,0:04:05.47,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,Could you please repeat that again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.47,0:04:07.47,Main,Kaigamori,0,0,0,,{\i1}What{\i0} was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.84,0:04:15.73,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Osato Naoko was a college student\N preparing to graduate during the coming spring... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.73,0:04:20.40,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}...but at the end of that September, \Nshe murdered her boyfriend.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.47,0:05:14.50,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Osato Naoko.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:21.46,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Her family had found success producing miso in Mutsukabe Hill \N for the last three hundred years, and she was their sole heir.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:28.01,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Their mansion was located \N at the end of a long dirt road.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:32.48,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Essentially, that entire mountain was\N private property of her family.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.00,0:05:41.94,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.42,0:05:44.15,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Can you go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.15,0:05:45.02,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.15,0:05:47.82,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,And put that game away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.20,0:05:51.99,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.99,0:05:54.25,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,Someone coming from the main building?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:05:57.67,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Just leave, okay?\N Go out the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:05:59.75,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,C'mon, Nao!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.75,0:06:04.92,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,Lately, it's like... \Nyou've been acting real cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:07.47,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,I hate thinking about it, \N but if there's another guy{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.37,0:06:12.96,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,This should be easy since you got the hint. {Nothing wrong translation-wise here, but this reads kinda awkwardly. -Starfish}{Is it more like "You should have already figured it out by now"? -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:17.27,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Let's leave our good times together in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.27,0:06:19.81,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,It's not like my dad would ever approve of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.81,0:06:21.94,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,You're just a part-time gardener.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.32,0:06:26.17,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I'm the only heir to our family fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.03,0:06:31.03,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,I'm not going anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.03,0:06:32.66,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,You gotta be kidding me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.66,0:06:35.91,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,What's wrong with how things are, Nao? {jesus his arm... that's some serious Part 1 manga anatomy}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.20,0:06:36.71,Secondary,Naoko,0,0,0,,Let go of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.91,0:06:37.79,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,There's no reason to break up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.17,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:42.42,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,How about we let \N the new guy and your dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:45.05,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,...catch me holding you like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.52,0:06:47.60,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I said let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.30,0:06:49.13,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,Wh{{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:50.43,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.55,0:06:54.22,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,S-Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:58.18,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,But... Y-You hit me first...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.18,0:07:01.15,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,I'm seriously in love with you, Nao.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:03.81,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,I'm okay with how things are.\N Nobody needs to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.81,0:07:05.78,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Get out! \N Get out and don't come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.78,0:07:07.40,Main,Gunpei,0,0,0,,Nao, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.40,0:07:11.53,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Get out! \NTake your money and leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.08,0:07:17.91,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,She may be in a bit of a tizzy \N since we're here unannounced.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.42,0:07:20.71,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be surprised if she's \N throwing on makeup right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.61,0:07:26.00,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Not good... They're headed this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:29.17,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Please, just take your things and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.67,0:07:31.59,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,To be honest with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.59,0:07:33.30,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,...I think you're amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.30,0:07:35.18,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,But he's my fiancé.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:38.81,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Our wedding was already \N arranged for next spring after I graduate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:40.69,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,That's why we're through!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.69,0:07:42.49,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,We can't keep doing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.46,0:07:46.32,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.35,0:07:53.46,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Gunpei?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.95,0:08:00.29,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.88,0:08:10.80,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.80,0:08:14.19,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,You're teasing me again...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.19,0:08:15.30,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,...aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.04,0:08:17.16,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Gunpei...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.19,0:08:19.57,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Quit fooling around!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.50,0:08:23.50,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,There's no pulse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.32,0:08:26.40,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,H-He's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.04,0:08:33.40,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Osato Naoko felt she should\N treat Gunpei's wound, at the very least.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.15,0:08:38.28,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}She covered it with a nearby towel.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.81,0:08:41.16,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,This is just another one of Gunpei's pranks...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:43.16,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Something here definitely doesn't add up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.16,0:08:45.32,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I barely even pushed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:51.46,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,What were those golf clubs even doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.46,0:08:55.26,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Why?!\N It looks like I... like I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.56,0:08:59.89,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,...like I hit him with a golf club!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.89,0:09:01.26,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Gunpei!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.92,0:09:03.72,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Wh-What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:06.56,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Doctor! \NI need to call a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.49,0:09:11.70,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,But can a doctor even help \N if he's already dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.23,0:09:16.09,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Should I call the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.45,0:09:20.83,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,Naoko, are you in there? It's Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.74,0:09:24.54,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,Shuichi's come to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.96,0:09:26.69,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,He's eager to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:35.59,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I'm gone... \NI'm not really here right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:38.28,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I don't exist anywhere anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.36,0:09:41.97,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,The door's locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.55,0:09:45.26,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,Could Naoko be out right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.73,0:09:52.73,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,I may have imagined it, sir, \N but I believe I saw the divider behind the window move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.84,0:10:00.62,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I... I have to hide him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:03.87,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,S-Somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.06,0:10:09.27,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I need to get Gunpei out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.68,0:10:12.00,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Under the sofa?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.90,0:10:16.92,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:20.43,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Even though he doesn't have a \N pulse and his heart stopped beating...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:22.05,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Why is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.99,0:10:25.10,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,Naoko, are you in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:29.10,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,What's the matter?\N This isn't like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.60,0:10:32.19,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,I have a spare key.\N I'll peek inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.19,0:10:33.61,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:35.57,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I-I didn't hear you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.57,0:10:37.53,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I was cleaning the kitchen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.95,0:10:40.99,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,Oh, Naoko, you're there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:42.91,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,Shuichi's come to visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.26,0:10:46.54,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,O-Oh, that's wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.54,0:10:48.54,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Wait in the main building, please! {Worth noting that she's NOT referring to the mansion here. Literally it's "the grounds' feudal estate," which is an older term with no English equivalent. -J} {No u. -A}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.03,0:10:51.46,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,You sound troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.46,0:10:53.54,Main,Dad McDadson,0,0,0,,Are you okay? \NDo you need help?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.54,0:10:56.05,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I'm fine! \NJust changing right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.05,0:10:59.68,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Don't come in!\N I'll be right with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.68,0:11:00.84,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,You'd better...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:05.35,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,You'd better not open that door!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.20,0:11:34.21,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Wh-What? \NWhat's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:37.67,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Do people normally \Nkeep bleeding after they die?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.11,0:11:40.35,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,Naoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:43.43,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,You've had the water running\N an awfully long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.43,0:11:44.80,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.53,0:11:50.25,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,It's Shuichi. \N Are you wondering why I'm still at the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:57.16,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,Actually, your dad gave me\N the spare key so we could be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.57,0:12:02.03,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,No! Don't! \N Don't you dare come in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.59,0:12:04.78,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,Naoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.68,0:12:10.58,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, \N I saw someone else through the window earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.62,0:12:14.21,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,There isn't actually anyone else in there, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.68,0:12:17.88,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,Are you {\i1}really{\i0} alone right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.88,0:12:21.72,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,I thought I saw someone else with you.{Rephrased this and Naoko's line ten lines below so the phrasing would match. They do in Japanese, so they should in English too. Also, what's this, a Starfish edit that actually SHORTENED a line?! What is this madness?!!! -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.52,0:12:26.68,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!\NI'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.68,0:12:28.72,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,But this is all your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.23,0:12:30.80,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything wrong! {Just like Homura and also Shinji. I'll let you decide which Shinji I'm talking about. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.99,0:12:50.79,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,Wh-What's wrong, Naoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.22,0:12:54.87,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,So someone else {\i1}is{\i0} in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.46,0:12:58.54,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Please, Gunpei!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:12:59.92,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.92,0:13:01.30,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Stop bleeding!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.05,0:13:06.59,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,I'm coming in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.42,0:13:39.59,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,You saw someone else in here with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:42.94,Main,Naoko,0,0,0,,Who did you think you saw, Shuichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.92,0:13:47.84,Thoughts,Naoko,0,0,0,,Oh... {yadda yadda comment back in if you're a dungus-bulungus bleeeeeee blooooo bleeeeeee -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.58,0:13:49.97,Thoughts,Naoko,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.97,0:13:51.18,Thoughts,Naoko,0,0,0,,Stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.18,0:13:52.34,Thoughts,Naoko,0,0,0,,Stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.93,0:13:55.35,Thoughts,Naoko,0,0,0,,Gunpei, forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.99,0:13:58.44,Thoughts,Naoko,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.18,0:14:01.12,Thoughts,Naoko,0,0,0,,Please forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:06.40,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,Sorry. I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.40,0:14:08.53,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,Guess my imagination was running wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.06,0:14:11.26,Main,Shuichi,0,0,0,,I'll wait with your dad in the main building. {Same as line 178 -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:25.09,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}As per their arrangement,\NOsato Naoko's wedding took place that spring...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:28.30,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and Shuichi became \Na son-in-law of the Osato family.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.53,0:14:31.51,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yet since that first day...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.51,0:14:33.26,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}...without fail...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.26,0:14:36.09,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}...Kamafusa Gunpei continued to bleed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.20,0:14:40.56,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}Each day he quietly bled \Nabout three-hundred cubic centimeters.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.56,0:14:45.07,Main,Rohan,0,0,0,,{\i1}So long as his body lay undisturbed...{\i0}
